3

gapminder::gapminder 70 

library(ggplot2)
gapminder %>% 
  filter(lifeExp>70) %>% 
  group_by(continent) %>% 
  summarise(n=n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=continent,y=n,fill=continent))+
  geom_bar(stat='identity')+
  labs(title=" 3",
       subtitle=" 70   ()",
       x="",y="")

4

gapminder::gapminder 70 .

library(ggplot2)
gapminder %>% 
  filter(lifeExp>70) %>% 
  group_by(continent,country) %>% 
  summarise(n=n()) %>% 
  group_by(continent) %>% 
  summarise(n=n())%>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=continent,y=n,fill=continent))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(title=" 4",
       subtitle=" 70    ",
       x="",y=" ")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'continent'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

  geom_point(aes(col=continent),alpha=0.6,pch=16)+
  facet_wrap(~year)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  #coord_cartesian(xlim=c(5,10000))

       subtitle="GDP  ",
       x="gdpPercap",y="lifeExp")
